  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So in August of '41, apparently, the Polish exile government in London signed a treaty with the Russians, with the Soviets, which provided for a number of things-- the creation of a Polish army in Russia, [INAUDIBLE], which was supposed to fight with the Russians.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The release of those people who had been at night, in June of 1940, sent to Siberia, and other people who had been earlier sent to Siberia, who were Polish citizens-- but who were Polish citizens, they made a point.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There were a couple of people there who claimed they were Czechs and English and other things, and where by coincidence, they wouldn't be released at the time.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We allegedly were allowed to go to wherever we wanted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We were supposed to get temporary documents stating that we were Poles, which in, which, which was, in a given time, had to be exchanged for Polish passports, the problem being that no consulate agreement had been signed, and there was no place to really exchange those, it turned out later.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were also restrictions.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
